shared_text:
Van Wert High School
August 5 at 1:15 PM ¬∑

Class schedule pick-up for Van Wert High School Students will be as follows:

Per the VWCS Reopening Plan- All students MUST wear a mask or other face-covering while in the building. Social distancing will be observed and expected. Students will be permitted to navigate the building in order to try lockers and locate classrooms. These are STUDENT ONLY dates. Students should enter via door H-18 (HS Gymnasium) and report to the Commons. Parents should wait in their vehicles.

Tuesday, August 11: Seniors from Noon ‚Äì 3:00 p.m.

Wednesday, August 12: Juniors from Noon ‚Äì 3:00 p.m.

Thursday, August 13: Sophomores from Noon ‚Äì 3:00 p.m.

Friday, August 14: Freshmen from Noon ‚Äì 3:00 p.m.

If you have any questions, please call the student services office at 419-238-2180.

post_text:
VWCS Family,

Governor DeWine has released his guidelines on Reset and Restart to School in the fall and we have been planning for the return to school in August. Van Wert City Schools is asking for your input and would like all stakeholders to complete the survey.

The survey will be open between Monday, July 13 through Sunday, July 19. We value your opinions, and more importantly, the safety of every student and staff member that comes to VWCS each day.

Please give us your honest feedback and we welcome your questions, concerns, and comments at any time by contacting Mark Bagley at 419-238-0648.

These are tough times, but as we always do, VWCS will figure this out and give our students the best education possible.

Thanks and Enjoy your Summer!

post_text: An important update from our friends at the YWCA of Van Wert County regarding the Summer Food Program.
shared_text:
YWCA of Van Wert County
April 30 at 12:00 PM ¬∑

Typically, right now we would be ramping up for the 25th year of our Summer Food Program.
While we are still wholly committed to this program, we have had to come to terms with the fact that it will most certainly look different this year. To protect the health and safety of our program attendees, our staff and our community, this year‚Äôs SFP meals will be served as ‚ÄúGrab and Go‚Äù, open to all children under the age of 18. The recreation portion of the program has been cancelled this year.

While we are disappointed to be unable to offer a summer filled with recreation for our participants, we are dedicated to ensuring that no child in Van Wert County goes hungry during the summer months. Please continue to check back for more updates in the coming weeks.
text:
An important update from our friends at the YWCA of Van Wert County regarding the Summer Food Program.

YWCA of Van Wert County
April 30 at 12:00 PM ¬∑

Typically, right now we would be ramping up for the 25th year of our Summer Food Program.
While we are still wholly committed to this program, we have had to come to terms with the fact that it will most certainly look different this year. To protect the health and safety of our program attendees, our staff and our community, this year‚Äôs SFP meals will be served as ‚ÄúGrab and Go‚Äù, open to all children under the age of 18. The recreation portion of the program has been cancelled this year.

While we are disappointed to be unable to offer a summer filled with recreation for our participants, we are dedicated to ensuring that no child in Van Wert County goes hungry during the summer months. Please continue to check back for more updates in the coming weeks.

So that Van Wert City Schools can better prepare meals for our district students, starting Monday, March 30th, 2020, we will begin providing our Grab and Go service two days a week from 10:45 A.M. to 1:00 P.M. All school meals will be distributed on Monday (for Monday and Tuesday's meals) and Wednesday (for Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday's meals).

Van Wert City Schools will continue to require that parents/students are to have each student identification number at the time of pickup. At this time, all meals are free for the child. For those interested, please complete this pre-order form. Meals can be picked up at the S.F. Goedde Building (doors #7 and #8) and the Ohio City Village Hall/Utility Office (North door of the council chambers).

Please click here for the pre-order form.üëâ https://forms.gle/heuVcq55Ke4o58CE9

This order form (to be filled out once per household) may be filled out at any time, and responses will be reviewed daily.

post_text:
EDIT: All school-related events will be cancelled, including extra-curriculars.

~ ~ ~

Van Wert City Schools has cancelled all classes beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, April 3 due to the order announced by Governor Mike DeWine on Thursday, March 12. VWCS will remain open for normal classes on Friday, March 13.

In a press conference today, Governor DeWine announced an order to close all K-12 schools throughout the state of Ohio for three weeks, at least through April 3.

Van Wert City Schools‚Äô spring break was already scheduled for March 16-20. VWCS will remain closed until April 3 and will announce its plan for distance-learning by the end of day on Friday, March 20.

VWCS will continue to work closely with the Van Wert Health Department, who is in contact with the Ohio Department of Health and the CDC, as we monitor the development of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19). Updates will be posted on the VWCS website, Facebook and Twitter pages.

EDIT: All school-related events will be cancelled, including extra-curriculars.

~ ~ ~

Van Wert City Schools has cancelled all classes beginning Monday, March 16 through Friday, April 3 due to the order announced by Governor Mike DeWine on Thursday, March 12. VWCS will remain open for normal classes on Friday, March 13.

In a press conference today, Governor DeWine announced an order to close all K-12 schools throughout the state of Ohio for three weeks, at least through April 3.

Van Wert City Schools‚Äô spring break was already scheduled for March 16-20. VWCS will remain closed until April 3 and will announce its plan for distance-learning by the end of day on Friday, March 20.

VWCS will continue to work closely with the Van Wert Health Department, who is in contact with the Ohio Department of Health and the CDC, as we monitor the development of coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID-19). Updates will be posted on the VWCS website, Facebook and Twitter pages.

There are currently no cases of COVID-19 in Van Wert County. At this time there are not any Persons Under Investigation (PUI). The Van Wert County General Health District is working closely with the schools on prevention of the spread and planning for the potential spread. We are encouraging schools to communicate with parents and caregivers and to help students to learn proper hygiene for prevention. There are NO schools closing in Van Wert County due to the COVID-19, and the health department is not requiring or recommending closure at this time.

Click to read the full statement released from the Van Wert County Health Department today.

Mr. Koontz continues to do amazing things for our students! Be sure to support his LifeChanger of the Year nomination by visiting his profile and leaving a positive comment. Or drop a comment here with the hashtag #LCOY! #EducationInnovationTradition #VWCougarPride

Mr. Koontz's profile page: http://app.lifechangeroftheyear.com/nomination_detail.cfm?NominationID=4245
shared_text:
APP.LIFECHANGEROFTHEYEAR.COM
Kerry Koontz

LifeChanger of the Year
February 27 at 5:00 PM ¬∑

Kerry Koontz has been in education for over 30 years, and has shown no signs of slowing down! A few years ago, he created an internship program so students at Van Wert High School and Van Wert City Schools could gain hands-on experience in a career field. Today, over 70 students and 35 businesses participate in the program. Because of his work, students have observed surgeries, interned for the local fire department, and gained full-time employment upon graduation. That's what being a LifeChanger's all about!

Van Wert County Foundation
February 23 at 10:45 AM ¬∑

Scholar Spotlight!

Meet LeAndryce Miller, 2019 VWCF Scholarship Recipient from the Julie M. Strete and Lawrence Bert Strete Memorial Scholarship Fund.

LeAndryce graduated from Van Wert High School in 2016 and is currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree in Diagnostic Medical Sonography-Abdominal and Obstetric-Gynecologic. She will graduate in April of 2020; and will be ARDMS board certified in the four sonography specialties of the abdominal, breast, OB-GYN, and vascular. After graduation, she plans on returning to the Van Wert area to pursue her career and be able to give back to the community.

‚ÄúThis scholarship program has helped me significantly reduce my student loan debt. It also helped me save money, and be able to pay for my board exams, by completely covering my housing for my senior year.‚Äù - LeAndryce

#VWCF #InspiringGrowth #BuildingTheFuture #VWCFScholar #vanwertOHIO #Scholarship #VanWertCountyCollaborates #Scholar
